INSERT INTO `news_articles` VALUES (1,'PLAYSTATION 0 - XBOX 3','',_binary '<p>The fight for players is getting tougher. Who loses, the brands or the players, we think it\'s clear,</p><p>Three games that can only be played on PC, PS4 and PS5 are moving to Xbox One, Xbox Series S and Xbox Series X.</p><p>The first of these three games is The Pathless. The action-adventure game developed by Giant Squid, The Pathless, was released on November 12, 2020 as a PS5 game.</p><p>The second game is Solar Ash, released on December 2, 2021 and coming to us from the Heart Machine development team. The sci-fi action adventure had a good score of 78 on Metacritic.</p><p>The third and final game so far is Maquette from developer Graceful Decay. It was released in 2021, but on March 2, and at the time of release, it was free via PS Plus. Puzzle adventure with Metacritic scores ranging from 70 to 71.</p><p>What do you think about this?</p>','PLAYSTATION 0 - XBOX 3','',_binary '<p>The fight for players is getting tougher. Who loses, the brands or the players, we think it\'s clear,</p><p>Three games that can only be played on PC, PS4 and PS5 are moving to Xbox One, Xbox Series S and Xbox Series X.</p><p>The first of these three games is The Pathless. The action-adventure game developed by Giant Squid, The Pathless, was released on November 12, 2020 as a PS5 game.</p><p>The second game is Solar Ash, released on December 2, 2021 and coming to us from the Heart Machine development team. The sci-fi action adventure had a good score of 78 on Metacritic.</p><p>The third and final game so far is Maquette from developer Graceful Decay. It was released in 2021, but on March 2, and at the time of release, it was free via PS Plus. Puzzle adventure with Metacritic scores ranging from 70 to 71.</p><p>What do you think about this?</p>','2022-08-07 11:01:34.223',1,0),(3,'FAN WORK ON RESIDENT EVIL UNREAL ENGINE 5','the story also depends on who is telling it... Or making it',_binary '<p>Despite the problems and setbacks when the series began to turn more towards action in the fifth and sixth installments, Resident Evil is back in top form. As well as being one of the most successful horror franchises in the industry, known for one of the most iconic save features in games, it has tweaked the classic formula to keep things fresh and has had a number of well-received remakes.</p><p>The first parts have been successfully brought back to life with more modern development methods, and it seems that another new old story is on the way. That is, the unofficial remake of Resident Evil is currently being worked on by an independent team. DSO Gaming spotted a short trailer showing how it\'s been done so far. The most interesting thing about this fan-made project is that it runs in Unreal Engine 5 and will apparently retain the fixed camera angles and tank controls of the original classic. Because of the engine it\'s being developed in, it looks pretty good so far.</p><p>At the time of writing, there doesn\'t seem to be a release date for this remake.</p><p>Fans always want to show their love for this long-running and influential franchise. There\'s a recent Resident Evil 9 concept video that fantastically showcases a possible scenario where the games\' main tyrants return, as well as a number of community-created remakes.</p><p>It\'s clear that the RE games have left a lasting impression on the gaming world, and players just want to see more stories from the main story.</p><p>Now seems like a good time to be a RE fan.</p><p>With Capcom working on a remake of Resident Evil 4, plus we have rumors that RE9 is officially in development, the classic horror franchise is by no means finished. Since the game was rebooted in 2017, taking it away from the action-oriented fifth and sixth installments, there has been a resurgence of interest in Resident Evil in general. This has been seen not only in the success of 2021\'s Village, but also in how fans want to get in on the action and create their own remakes and remasters.</p><p>Resident Evil was originally released in 1996 on the PlayStation and was later ported to the Nintendo DS, PC and Sega Saturn.</p>','FAN WORK ON RESIDENT EVIL UNREAL ENGINE 5','the story also depends on who is telling it... Or making it',_binary '<p>Despite the problems and setbacks when the series began to turn more towards action in the fifth and sixth installments, Resident Evil is back in top form. As well as being one of the most successful horror franchises in the industry, known for one of the most iconic save features in games, it has tweaked the classic formula to keep things fresh and has had a number of well-received remakes.</p><p>The first parts have been successfully brought back to life with more modern development methods, and it seems that another new old story is on the way. That is, the unofficial remake of Resident Evil is currently being worked on by an independent team. DSO Gaming spotted a short trailer showing how it\'s been done so far. The most interesting thing about this fan-made project is that it runs in Unreal Engine 5 and will apparently retain the fixed camera angles and tank controls of the original classic. Because of the engine it\'s being developed in, it looks pretty good so far.</p><p>At the time of writing, there doesn\'t seem to be a release date for this remake.</p><p>Fans always want to show their love for this long-running and influential franchise. There\'s a recent Resident Evil 9 concept video that fantastically showcases a possible scenario where the games\' main tyrants return, as well as a number of community-created remakes.</p><p>It\'s clear that the RE games have left a lasting impression on the gaming world, and players just want to see more stories from the main story.</p><p>Now seems like a good time to be a RE fan.</p><p>With Capcom working on a remake of Resident Evil 4, plus we have rumors that RE9 is officially in development, the classic horror franchise is by no means finished. Since the game was rebooted in 2017, taking it away from the action-oriented fifth and sixth installments, there has been a resurgence of interest in Resident Evil in general. This has been seen not only in the success of 2021\'s Village, but also in how fans want to get in on the action and create their own remakes and remasters.</p><p>Resident Evil was originally released in 1996 on the PlayStation and was later ported to the Nintendo DS, PC and Sega Saturn.</p>','2022-08-15 12:08:05.232',0,0),(4,'TINY TINA WONDERLANDS','What is certain is that the level of dopamine increases during the whole game, keeping you awake and active, almost \"on tingles\". If this is what you need, Tiny Tina Wonderlands is the right overworld for you.',_binary '<p>BORDERLANDS</p><p>Let\'s go back in time first, shall we? \"Little\" is a relative term, and for me it has been here for more than a decade. Thirteen years, to be exact. In 2009, Gearbox Software, in cooperation with 2K Games, created and published the forerunner of the aforementioned game under the name Borderlands. Good and evil, heroes and enemies, battles and fighters, losses and victories - every game has all these elements, right? However, not every game gets nearly as much credit or recognition as Borderlands.</p><p>IS IT WORTH PLAYING?</p><p>This March, Borderlands is getting a new sequel â€“ Tiny Tina Wonderlands. And this game is accompanied by a well-known dilemma: is it worth playing? Apart from similar associations to the very mention of the game (one can say prejudice), it features many famous characters as well as the way of playing. It also brings some innovations, but retains the spirit and many features of its predecessors, so it\'s no wonder that this dilemma persists even now. The chip doesn\'t fall far from the log, does it? Especially if its creators don\'t want it, but stick firmly to their standards.</p><p>This is, in a way, a good thing - they think there are good sides to their standards, and by that they mean that the standards are quite different from anything else in the gaming world. And why change something, if it still has an effect?</p><p>THE PLAYERS</p><p>You can play the game alone or with up to three players, but even when playing with someone, you retain some of your individuality and uniqueness. By that I mean that the team doesn\'t play that big of a role here; everyone has their own imagination that they use to create their own path, strategy and game plan, so they don\'t depend on the rest of the team.</p><p>While in some games communication, teamwork, knowing your teammates, their flaws and weaknesses are crucial, this is not the case here. Everyone is their own, in a way, a bit narcissistic and self-sufficient.</p><p>In addition, anyone can make their character exactly how they want it, if we consider that every aspect of physical appearance is taken into account.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/tiny-tinas-wonderlands-character-customization.jpg\"></p><p>WEAPON</p><p>What especially attracts attention are weapons that can completely change the way of playing, as well as the course of the fight. And everything changes quite quickly. If, for example, you choose a hammer instead of a gun, the way you move, kill, how enemies die - everything changes. Although, this is also known from previous games from this franchise. A newspaper is a book of spells. Acts are fun and contextually relevant, tailored to the story and substance. They can be used on individual enemies as well as groups of them.</p><p>ENEMIES</p><p>What has angered and disappointed many is that there isn\'t a huge variety of enemies. Although everything changes quickly and often, the enemies remain similar from the beginning to the end of the gameplay. They don\'t all increase in strength like in many games, they don\'t get stronger over time, they stay the same, which is frustrating. If you already level up, the fight should be harder, right? Yes, there are bigger bosses with unique characteristics, but those opportunities are quite rare. This is precisely why this latest game in the franchise feels easier than the previous ones.</p><p>THE ENVIRONMENT</p><p>One of the more interesting details is the environment itself - juice and popcorn everywhere in this \"world\", pointing to the fact that, as one of the players said, at the end of the day, this is all just fun between friends.</p><p>In addition to this, everything is quite colorful, vivid, creative, full of small details that sometimes distract attention. At least until you get used to them, especially if you\'re used to drier locations.</p><p>Beanstalks, greenery, rivers, bays, old buildings and friendly cyclops eager to explore the archeology of their place are things you can expect to see at every turn.</p>','TINY TINA WONDERLANDS','What is certain is that the level of dopamine increases during the whole game, keeping you awake and active, almost \"on tingles\". If this is what you need, Tiny Tina Wonderlands is the right overworld for you.',_binary '<p>BORDERLANDS</p><p>Let\'s go back in time first, shall we? \"Little\" is a relative term, and for me it has been here for more than a decade. Thirteen years, to be exact. In 2009, Gearbox Software, in cooperation with 2K Games, created and published the forerunner of the aforementioned game under the name Borderlands. Good and evil, heroes and enemies, battles and fighters, losses and victories - every game has all these elements, right? However, not every game gets nearly as much credit or recognition as Borderlands.</p><p>IS IT WORTH PLAYING?</p><p>This March, Borderlands is getting a new sequel â€“ Tiny Tina Wonderlands. And this game is accompanied by a well-known dilemma: is it worth playing? Apart from similar associations to the very mention of the game (one can say prejudice), it features many famous characters as well as the way of playing. It also brings some innovations, but retains the spirit and many features of its predecessors, so it\'s no wonder that this dilemma persists even now. The chip doesn\'t fall far from the log, does it? Especially if its creators don\'t want it, but stick firmly to their standards.</p><p>This is, in a way, a good thing - they think there are good sides to their standards, and by that they mean that the standards are quite different from anything else in the gaming world. And why change something, if it still has an effect?</p><p>THE PLAYERS</p><p>You can play the game alone or with up to three players, but even when playing with someone, you retain some of your individuality and uniqueness. By that I mean that the team doesn\'t play that big of a role here; everyone has their own imagination that they use to create their own path, strategy and game plan, so they don\'t depend on the rest of the team.</p><p>While in some games communication, teamwork, knowing your teammates, their flaws and weaknesses are crucial, this is not the case here. Everyone is their own, in a way, a bit narcissistic and self-sufficient.</p><p>In addition, anyone can make their character exactly how they want it, if we consider that every aspect of physical appearance is taken into account.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/tiny-tinas-wonderlands-character-customization.jpg\"></p><p>WEAPON</p><p>What especially attracts attention are weapons that can completely change the way of playing, as well as the course of the fight. And everything changes quite quickly. If, for example, you choose a hammer instead of a gun, the way you move, kill, how enemies die - everything changes. Although, this is also known from previous games from this franchise. A newspaper is a book of spells. Acts are fun and contextually relevant, tailored to the story and substance. They can be used on individual enemies as well as groups of them.</p><p>ENEMIES</p><p>What has angered and disappointed many is that there isn\'t a huge variety of enemies. Although everything changes quickly and often, the enemies remain similar from the beginning to the end of the gameplay. They don\'t all increase in strength like in many games, they don\'t get stronger over time, they stay the same, which is frustrating. If you already level up, the fight should be harder, right? Yes, there are bigger bosses with unique characteristics, but those opportunities are quite rare. This is precisely why this latest game in the franchise feels easier than the previous ones.</p><p>THE ENVIRONMENT</p><p>One of the more interesting details is the environment itself - juice and popcorn everywhere in this \"world\", pointing to the fact that, as one of the players said, at the end of the day, this is all just fun between friends.</p><p>In addition to this, everything is quite colorful, vivid, creative, full of small details that sometimes distract attention. At least until you get used to them, especially if you\'re used to drier locations.</p><p>Beanstalks, greenery, rivers, bays, old buildings and friendly cyclops eager to explore the archeology of their place are things you can expect to see at every turn.</p>','2022-08-10 19:34:25.145',1,0),(5,'The first Starfield gameplay: Build, crew and actually fly a spaceship','You build, crew and actually fly a spaceship',_binary '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Xbox and Bethesda Showcase has finally delivered what everyone has been waiting for so long!</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Fans finally got what they\'ve been wanting since 2018. The first trailer for the Starfield game is here. Bethesda also answered some burning questions about space travel, planetary exploration, and more. For those wondering if planets will function like Skyrim dungeons with separate instances representing a small playable area, they won\'t.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Starfield will have 100 different star systems and over 1000 different planets. And according to Todd Howard, all of those planets will be fully explorable. Land anywhere, on any planet, get out and start exploring.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">We see some things about the game from the trailer. The player lands on a new planet, observes some alien life forms and mines some resources from a stone wall. He then finds a facility under pirate control. There is gunplay, grenades are thrown, and a space rifle is used to finish off bandits. The player finds new weapons before facing more pirates outside, using the jetpack to launch himself across the gap and engage more enemies. The action then shifts to the capital, New Atlantis, to meet a few NPCs and have a brief discussion about mysterious artifacts and \"visions.\"</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/starfield.jpg\"></p><p><br></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">After that, Todd Howard takes a look at Starfield\'s character creation tools and starting traits, which include pros and cons, and the skill system you unlock as you level up. And finally the long-standing question was answered.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">You\'ll be able to build your own spaceship and populate it with NPCs of your choice.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">And yes, you can fly. You can really fly!</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Ship-to-ship combat in space? Confirmed.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">The spaceship has been speculated to serve as a loading screen or fast travel point, but the trailer shows how it actually moves, from system to system and planet to planet. We were expecting Skyrim in space, but... It looks more like Fallout in space.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/starfield2.jpg\"></p><p><br></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">One thing is certain for now: with 1000 different planets, it looks much bigger than any Bethesda RPG to date.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">It\'s been a long wait, hasn\'t it? It was first announced at Bethesda\'s E3 press conference back in 2018. It took another three years before the official theatrical teaser trailer was shown in June 2021. It was originally scheduled to be released on 11/11. 22, and Bethesda announced in May that Starfield would be delayed until 2023.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">We may still not be sure when we will play it, but at least we know what we will be able to play.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zmb2FJGvnAw\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zmb2FJGvnAw</a></p>','The first Starfield gameplay: Build, crew and actually fly a spaceship','You build, crew and actually fly a spaceship',_binary '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Xbox and Bethesda Showcase has finally delivered what everyone has been waiting for so long!</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Fans finally got what they\'ve been wanting since 2018. The first trailer for the Starfield game is here. Bethesda also answered some burning questions about space travel, planetary exploration, and more. For those wondering if planets will function like Skyrim dungeons with separate instances representing a small playable area, they won\'t.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Starfield will have 100 different star systems and over 1000 different planets. And according to Todd Howard, all of those planets will be fully explorable. Land anywhere, on any planet, get out and start exploring.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">We see some things about the game from the trailer. The player lands on a new planet, observes some alien life forms and mines some resources from a stone wall. He then finds a facility under pirate control. There is gunplay, grenades are thrown, and a space rifle is used to finish off bandits. The player finds new weapons before facing more pirates outside, using the jetpack to launch himself across the gap and engage more enemies. The action then shifts to the capital, New Atlantis, to meet a few NPCs and have a brief discussion about mysterious artifacts and \"visions.\"</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/starfield.jpg\"></p><p><br></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">After that, Todd Howard takes a look at Starfield\'s character creation tools and starting traits, which include pros and cons, and the skill system you unlock as you level up. And finally the long-standing question was answered.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">You\'ll be able to build your own spaceship and populate it with NPCs of your choice.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">And yes, you can fly. You can really fly!</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Ship-to-ship combat in space? Confirmed.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">The spaceship has been speculated to serve as a loading screen or fast travel point, but the trailer shows how it actually moves, from system to system and planet to planet. We were expecting Skyrim in space, but... It looks more like Fallout in space.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/starfield2.jpg\"></p><p><br></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">One thing is certain for now: with 1000 different planets, it looks much bigger than any Bethesda RPG to date.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">It\'s been a long wait, hasn\'t it? It was first announced at Bethesda\'s E3 press conference back in 2018. It took another three years before the official theatrical teaser trailer was shown in June 2021. It was originally scheduled to be released on 11/11. 22, and Bethesda announced in May that Starfield would be delayed until 2023.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">We may still not be sure when we will play it, but at least we know what we will be able to play.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zmb2FJGvnAw\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zmb2FJGvnAw</a></p>','2022-08-16 19:33:37.005',0,0),(6,'NEW POKEMON HAVE NEW VEHICLES MOTORS, BOATS AND PLANES','We\'ve got new details on the upcoming Pokemon Scarlet and Violet game',_binary '<p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">Pokemon Scarlet and Violet will offer fans role-playing in a completely open world for the first time. Running around that world would be slow, so the folks at the Game Freak development studio decided to add some gas. Namely, the Pokemon Koraidon and Miraidon will be the main transportation, so they are now able to drive the player on the ground, sail or fly.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">At the start of the game, players will join Naranja or Uva Academy (depending on the version of the game) and will go on a treasure hunt around the Paladea region. The game will be divided into three main stories. One story is classic - you have eight halls to conquer by defeating their trainers in PokÃ©mon battles. The remaining two stories have not yet been revealed,</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">One of the new activities will be Raid battles, where you can catch rare types of Tera Pokemon. In these battles, up to four players will be able to attack the opponent\'s Tera Pokemon together without having to wait for their turn - they all attack simultaneously, that is, according to their own rhythm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">So Pokemon Scarlet and Violet will have a cooperative multiplayer mode, but it has been confirmed that there will be no local play with a single copy of the game on one console. Each player must have their own copy of the game on their console. And yes, both players must then still have a subscription to Nintendo Switch Online.</span></p>','NEW POKEMON HAVE NEW VEHICLES MOTORS, BOATS AND PLANES','We\'ve got new details on the upcoming Pokemon Scarlet and Violet game',_binary '<p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">Pokemon Scarlet and Violet will offer fans role-playing in a completely open world for the first time. Running around that world would be slow, so the folks at the Game Freak development studio decided to add some gas. Namely, the Pokemon Koraidon and Miraidon will be the main transportation, so they are now able to drive the player on the ground, sail or fly.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">At the start of the game, players will join Naranja or Uva Academy (depending on the version of the game) and will go on a treasure hunt around the Paladea region. The game will be divided into three main stories. One story is classic - you have eight halls to conquer by defeating their trainers in PokÃ©mon battles. The remaining two stories have not yet been revealed,</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">One of the new activities will be Raid battles, where you can catch rare types of Tera Pokemon. In these battles, up to four players will be able to attack the opponent\'s Tera Pokemon together without having to wait for their turn - they all attack simultaneously, that is, according to their own rhythm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-font-monospace\">So Pokemon Scarlet and Violet will have a cooperative multiplayer mode, but it has been confirmed that there will be no local play with a single copy of the game on one console. Each player must have their own copy of the game on their console. And yes, both players must then still have a subscription to Nintendo Switch Online.</span></p>','2022-08-17 14:04:03.220',0,0),(7,'GOD OF WAR: RAGNARÃ–K PREORDER HAS BEGUN','The most beloved BOY! the simulator is among us again',_binary '<p>Whether RagnarÃ¶k is the beginning of the end of Kratos\' epic will remain a mystery until November. In the meantime, we will have the opportunity to live on \"crumbs\" of information and a mountain of theories that we will grab from every possible frame of every teaser or trailer of the game.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/gow_Reveal_Screenshot_Watermarked_13_090121%20(12).png\"></p><p>It\'s not the least bit of a surprise that the developers from the Santa Monica studio made a special effort to use all the unique capabilities of the PlayStation 5 consoles and the accompanying DualSense controllers, so it was announced to us that the game will be able to \"drive\" on two graphics settings:</p><p>full 4K resolution at 30 fps</p><p>up to 4K dynamic resolution at a targeted 60 fps</p><p>while DualSense will create a complete atmosphere in our hands thanks to adaptive triggers and haptic vibrations,</p><p>God of War: RagnarÃ¶k has also been ported to PlayStation 4 with exceptional optimization that will ensure that no PlayStation player and fan misses out on this experience.</p>','GOD OF WAR: RAGNARÃ–K PREORDER HAS BEGUN','The most beloved BOY! the simulator is among us again',_binary '<p>Whether RagnarÃ¶k is the beginning of the end of Kratos\' epic will remain a mystery until November. In the meantime, we will have the opportunity to live on \"crumbs\" of information and a mountain of theories that we will grab from every possible frame of every teaser or trailer of the game.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/gow_Reveal_Screenshot_Watermarked_13_090121%20(12).png\"></p><p>It\'s not the least bit of a surprise that the developers from the Santa Monica studio made a special effort to use all the unique capabilities of the PlayStation 5 consoles and the accompanying DualSense controllers, so it was announced to us that the game will be able to \"drive\" on two graphics settings:</p><p>full 4K resolution at 30 fps</p><p>up to 4K dynamic resolution at a targeted 60 fps</p><p>while DualSense will create a complete atmosphere in our hands thanks to adaptive triggers and haptic vibrations,</p><p>God of War: RagnarÃ¶k has also been ported to PlayStation 4 with exceptional optimization that will ensure that no PlayStation player and fan misses out on this experience.</p>','2022-07-15 14:07:30.997',1,0),(8,'STAR WARS JEDI: FALLEN ORDER 2','Will we be watching the Showcase as part of the Star Wars Celebration in May?',_binary '<p>Jeff Grubb claims that Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order 2 will definitely have its showcase during May\'s Star Wars Celebration.</p><p>This ties in with previous comments Grubb made in January, when he said we should expect to hear more about the game in a significant way before E3, with a possible May date. So it looks like the Star Wars Celebration has been booked, although nothing is official yet. Grubb also said in the video that Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order 2 is likely to be released in early 2023, but didn\'t rule out a late 2022 launch.</p><p>The original Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order was released for PS4, PC and Xbox One in November 2019, and was later released for PS5 and Xbox Series X/S last summer.</p>','STAR WARS JEDI: FALLEN ORDER 2','Will we be watching the Showcase as part of the Star Wars Celebration in May?',_binary '<p>Jeff Grubb claims that Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order 2 will definitely have its showcase during May\'s Star Wars Celebration.</p><p>This ties in with previous comments Grubb made in January, when he said we should expect to hear more about the game in a significant way before E3, with a possible May date. So it looks like the Star Wars Celebration has been booked, although nothing is official yet. Grubb also said in the video that Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order 2 is likely to be released in early 2023, but didn\'t rule out a late 2022 launch.</p><p>The original Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order was released for PS4, PC and Xbox One in November 2019, and was later released for PS5 and Xbox Series X/S last summer.</p>','2022-03-25 14:10:54.163',1,0),(9,'HOGWARTS LEGACY - WE ALSO GOT A RELEASE DATE','The predictions were correct',_binary '<p>Hogwarts Legacy, an open-world Harry Potter adventure set in the famous wizarding school, will launch during the 2022 holiday season for PlayStation 4, PlayStation 5, Windows PC, Xbox One and Xbox Series X.</p><p>Avalanche Software and Sony Interactive Entertainment showed off 15 minutes of gameplay yesterday during a State of Play live stream dedicated only to Hogwarts Legacy. Players were given a look at character creation in the game, some of the activities they\'ll encounter inside and outside of school, and a brief introduction to the story that ties it all together.</p><p>Hogwarts Legacy is set in the late 1800s, about 100 years before Harry Potter enrolled. In Hogwarts Legacy, the player character is a new wizard or witch, except they start as a fifth year student. So, the introduction will introduce players to the game\'s systems and controls, as well as introduce the character to the current story. It involves some sort of intrigue that brings in goblins and dark wizards. The tutorial stages seem to involve exploring the Goblin Rebellion with a brand new NPC, Professor Figg/o. Later in the 15-minute trailer, a \"darker path\" is hinted at, should players choose to follow it.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/5cc80560-a636-11ec-bddf-85b7cba14669.jpg\"></p><p>Hogwarts Legacy also seems to touch on all the familiar traits of an action RPG, including crafting (both potions and magic items), skill trees, and friend and follower parties, where NPCs add special talents to the adventuring party. The yacht\'s secret room, the Room of Requirement, can be found inside the academy and serves as a customizable hub between story missions. Although the game fits into the overall Harry Potter canon, creator JK Rowling was not involved in the creation of Hogwarts Legacy. Right after releasing Hogwarts Legacy in September 2020, the latest games from Warner Bros. they took the project away from her because of the public and transphobic remarks she made about gender.</p><p>The success of the game will certainly be closely watched. Many LGBTQ advocates have already renounced their once beloved fandom and feel that supporting the game is a direct endorsement of Rowling and her views. Others also noted that the game\'s former lead designer had a YouTube channel through which he supported right-wing factions and aired similar cultural grievances. That developer left Avalanche Software under unexplained circumstances in March 2021.</p><p>And once everything was so simple, the game was either good or bad.</p><p>How did you like State of Play?</p>','HOGWARTS LEGACY - WE ALSO GOT A RELEASE DATE','The predictions were correct',_binary '<p>Hogwarts Legacy, an open-world Harry Potter adventure set in the famous wizarding school, will launch during the 2022 holiday season for PlayStation 4, PlayStation 5, Windows PC, Xbox One and Xbox Series X.</p><p>Avalanche Software and Sony Interactive Entertainment showed off 15 minutes of gameplay yesterday during a State of Play live stream dedicated only to Hogwarts Legacy. Players were given a look at character creation in the game, some of the activities they\'ll encounter inside and outside of school, and a brief introduction to the story that ties it all together.</p><p>Hogwarts Legacy is set in the late 1800s, about 100 years before Harry Potter enrolled. In Hogwarts Legacy, the player character is a new wizard or witch, except they start as a fifth year student. So, the introduction will introduce players to the game\'s systems and controls, as well as introduce the character to the current story. It involves some sort of intrigue that brings in goblins and dark wizards. The tutorial stages seem to involve exploring the Goblin Rebellion with a brand new NPC, Professor Figg/o. Later in the 15-minute trailer, a \"darker path\" is hinted at, should players choose to follow it.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/5cc80560-a636-11ec-bddf-85b7cba14669.jpg\"></p><p>Hogwarts Legacy also seems to touch on all the familiar traits of an action RPG, including crafting (both potions and magic items), skill trees, and friend and follower parties, where NPCs add special talents to the adventuring party. The yacht\'s secret room, the Room of Requirement, can be found inside the academy and serves as a customizable hub between story missions. Although the game fits into the overall Harry Potter canon, creator JK Rowling was not involved in the creation of Hogwarts Legacy. Right after releasing Hogwarts Legacy in September 2020, the latest games from Warner Bros. they took the project away from her because of the public and transphobic remarks she made about gender.</p><p>The success of the game will certainly be closely watched. Many LGBTQ advocates have already renounced their once beloved fandom and feel that supporting the game is a direct endorsement of Rowling and her views. Others also noted that the game\'s former lead designer had a YouTube channel through which he supported right-wing factions and aired similar cultural grievances. That developer left Avalanche Software under unexplained circumstances in March 2021.</p><p>And once everything was so simple, the game was either good or bad.</p><p>How did you like State of Play?</p>','2022-03-18 14:13:02.264',1,0),(10,'GHOSTWIRE: TOKYO - A PARANORMAL MYSTERY IN NORMAL TOKYO','Tango Gameworks perfectly balances the two worlds',_binary '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Ghostwire: Tokyo was interesting to everyone from the first announcement. The subject is more than interesting: the citizens of Tokyo disappear, and mysterious invaders from another world, known as Visitors, begin to lurk in the streets.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the first two chapters of Ghostwire: Tokyo, players are introduced to 2-3 interconnected, but highly intriguing stories. Without wanting to post spoilers, what\'s impressive is how the game manages to introduce its enemies, develop the relationship between Akito and KK, and more, all without much exposition. Players are thrust right into the mystery, and just as Akito has to wrap his head and share his body with KK to fight the Visitors, so do the players.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/ss_67c79411e5b14f370cefce560e84553027d210db_1920x1080.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">This world building and story development permeates every aspect of the game, including the introduction. Through KK, Ghostwire: Tokyo players gain access to otherworldly powers like Ethereal Weaving. Using Kuji-Kiri hand gestures, further stylized for Ghostwire: Tokyo\'s own identity, players unleash special spiritual attacks fused with the elements.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">The game is unexpected, changing and addictive.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the moments when players explore and search for hidden secrets in the world of Ghostwire: Tokyo, it could even be said to be reminiscent of Batman: Arkham. And no hard feelings, for those considering whether to play, comparisons are important. They are essential to really show how the worlds come together. But... the thing is, none of these comparisons really show what matters, the cohesiveness of the experience. Every single aspect of Ghostwire: Tokyo feels connected and dependent on the others, so nothing feels out of place and, despite the paranormal elements, everything feels completely alive and breathing. All of the above serve the purpose of the game well and fit deeply rooted in the beautiful world. Where Ghostwire: Tokyo really shines is the world around the player. With no enemies around the game is playable and makes you feel like Grand Theft Auto set in Tokyo at night. Buildings, streets, avenues and more look incredibly realistic and inspire players to search every nook and cranny to complete the various side quests in Ghostwire: Tokyo. Hook on to the Yokai to climb the building or simply take the stairs as this is a world built and ready to explore.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/64d31790-85c5-11ec-bfa7-68f6d1448f50_cf.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Now take all of the above and add the paranormal to it!</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">It really takes the atmosphere to the next level. Achieving a balance between such a realistic representation of the city, with paranormal enemies and elements seems very difficult. When asked how they found this balance, Tango Gameworks director Kenji Kimura and producer Masato Kimura, who developed Ghostwire: Tokyo, said they walked around the city, recreated it, and used their imaginations to apply paranormal elements to the tops of buildings, Torii gates, and more. aspects. Kimura further commented:</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">From there, there\'s a lot of iteration that had to happen because we had one of our designers who was solely focused on applying paranormal effects to the city. We\'d try different things, he\'d show it to the director, and we\'d have a lot of back-and-forth discussions about, â€œThis looks too much. We\'ve gone too far.\"</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/Screenshot.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Indeed, this recreation of the city, laced with the paranormal, shines through every level of Ghostwire: Tokyo. The paranormal adds a creepy atmosphere and effects, while the realism keeps players glued to the game combined with the story and enemies. Players may be fighting otherworldly enemies, but it feels very natural.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Developer Tango stated and described their approach as wanting to make these enemies feel normal or natural before you approach them. From a distance, some Yokai look like businessmen. Up close, they have no face. And indeed, they perfectly use that fine balance between paranormal and realism. This creates a unique, eerie atmosphere that befits a horror game, even though Ghostwire: Tokyo is not a horror game. This is an action-adventure game that pushes the boundaries between action, adventure and horror. Some fans of past Tango Gameworks titles, specifically The Evil Within and The Evil Within 2, were understandably upset about the move away from horror. Ghostwire: Tokyo was originally billed as The Evil Within 3, and it shows. One important aspect of any horror game is the atmosphere it creates, and these elements simply shine through Ghostwire: Tokyo. In fact, the game is better because of them. It may not be terrifying, but it is scary, disturbing, and occasionally downright scary. It is precisely this eerie atmosphere that brings the need to react urgently and quickly and gives intensity to action and research.</p>','GHOSTWIRE: TOKYO - A PARANORMAL MYSTERY IN NORMAL TOKYO','Tango Gameworks perfectly balances the two worlds',_binary '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Ghostwire: Tokyo was interesting to everyone from the first announcement. The subject is more than interesting: the citizens of Tokyo disappear, and mysterious invaders from another world, known as Visitors, begin to lurk in the streets.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the first two chapters of Ghostwire: Tokyo, players are introduced to 2-3 interconnected, but highly intriguing stories. Without wanting to post spoilers, what\'s impressive is how the game manages to introduce its enemies, develop the relationship between Akito and KK, and more, all without much exposition. Players are thrust right into the mystery, and just as Akito has to wrap his head and share his body with KK to fight the Visitors, so do the players.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/ss_67c79411e5b14f370cefce560e84553027d210db_1920x1080.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">This world building and story development permeates every aspect of the game, including the introduction. Through KK, Ghostwire: Tokyo players gain access to otherworldly powers like Ethereal Weaving. Using Kuji-Kiri hand gestures, further stylized for Ghostwire: Tokyo\'s own identity, players unleash special spiritual attacks fused with the elements.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">The game is unexpected, changing and addictive.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the moments when players explore and search for hidden secrets in the world of Ghostwire: Tokyo, it could even be said to be reminiscent of Batman: Arkham. And no hard feelings, for those considering whether to play, comparisons are important. They are essential to really show how the worlds come together. But... the thing is, none of these comparisons really show what matters, the cohesiveness of the experience. Every single aspect of Ghostwire: Tokyo feels connected and dependent on the others, so nothing feels out of place and, despite the paranormal elements, everything feels completely alive and breathing. All of the above serve the purpose of the game well and fit deeply rooted in the beautiful world. Where Ghostwire: Tokyo really shines is the world around the player. With no enemies around the game is playable and makes you feel like Grand Theft Auto set in Tokyo at night. Buildings, streets, avenues and more look incredibly realistic and inspire players to search every nook and cranny to complete the various side quests in Ghostwire: Tokyo. Hook on to the Yokai to climb the building or simply take the stairs as this is a world built and ready to explore.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/64d31790-85c5-11ec-bfa7-68f6d1448f50_cf.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Now take all of the above and add the paranormal to it!</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">It really takes the atmosphere to the next level. Achieving a balance between such a realistic representation of the city, with paranormal enemies and elements seems very difficult. When asked how they found this balance, Tango Gameworks director Kenji Kimura and producer Masato Kimura, who developed Ghostwire: Tokyo, said they walked around the city, recreated it, and used their imaginations to apply paranormal elements to the tops of buildings, Torii gates, and more. aspects. Kimura further commented:</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">From there, there\'s a lot of iteration that had to happen because we had one of our designers who was solely focused on applying paranormal effects to the city. We\'d try different things, he\'d show it to the director, and we\'d have a lot of back-and-forth discussions about, â€œThis looks too much. We\'ve gone too far.\"</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://www.games.rs/files/images/Screenshot.jpg\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Indeed, this recreation of the city, laced with the paranormal, shines through every level of Ghostwire: Tokyo. The paranormal adds a creepy atmosphere and effects, while the realism keeps players glued to the game combined with the story and enemies. Players may be fighting otherworldly enemies, but it feels very natural.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Developer Tango stated and described their approach as wanting to make these enemies feel normal or natural before you approach them. From a distance, some Yokai look like businessmen. Up close, they have no face. And indeed, they perfectly use that fine balance between paranormal and realism. This creates a unique, eerie atmosphere that befits a horror game, even though Ghostwire: Tokyo is not a horror game. This is an action-adventure game that pushes the boundaries between action, adventure and horror. Some fans of past Tango Gameworks titles, specifically The Evil Within and The Evil Within 2, were understandably upset about the move away from horror. Ghostwire: Tokyo was originally billed as The Evil Within 3, and it shows. One important aspect of any horror game is the atmosphere it creates, and these elements simply shine through Ghostwire: Tokyo. In fact, the game is better because of them. It may not be terrifying, but it is scary, disturbing, and occasionally downright scary. It is precisely this eerie atmosphere that brings the need to react urgently and quickly and gives intensity to action and research.</p>','2022-03-15 14:16:29.524',1,0);
